<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="ios_basesetf" id="ios_basesetf">ios_base::setf</a></h2>
<div class="level2">
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    fmtflags setf<span class="br0">&#40;</span> fmtflags fl <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span>
    fmtflags setf<span class="br0">&#40;</span> fmtflags fl, fmtflags mask <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>

<br/>

</p>

<p>
Sets the formatting flags to specified settings. The first version just sets <code>fl</code> flags. The second version clears the flags under mask, and applies <code>fl &amp; mask</code> to them.
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT1 SECTION "ios_base::setf" [1-303] -->
<h3 class="sectionedit2"><a name="parameters" id="parameters">Parameters</a></h3>
<div class="level3">

<p>

<code>fl</code> - flag(s) to apply
</p>

<p>
<code>mask</code> - flag value defining which flags to edit
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT2 SECTION "Parameters" [304-402] -->
<h3 class="sectionedit3"><a name="return_value" id="return_value">Return value</a></h3>
<div class="level3">

<p>

formatting flags before the call
</p>

</div>
